OL,3,CTeenager has leg amputated after
OL,4,Cstabbing at Barry Island
OL,6,FA teenager has been forced to have his
OL,7,Fleg amputated after a stabbing in
OL,8,FBarry Island.
OL,10,FSouth Wales Police have confirmed they
OL,11,Fare continuing to investigate a
OL,12,Fstabbing which took place at Barry
OL,13,FIsland on Bank Holiday Monday (May 25).
OL,15,FA 17-year-old boy from Cardiff
OL,16,Fsuffered a serious leg injury which
OL,17,Fwas initially described as not
OL,18,Fbelieved to be life threatening or
OL,19,Flife changing.
